SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 850
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Tyson Sutton of
Gatlinburg-Pittman High School upon being
named All-County in football.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to recognize and
commend those successful high school athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring
honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Tyson Sutton of Gatlinburg-Pittman High
School in Sevier County, an athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who has proven
himself a formidable competitor on the football field; and
WHEREAS, Tyson Sutton was recently named to the All-County team in recognition of
his excellence on the gridiron for Gatlinburg-Pittman High School; and
WHEREAS, a junior quarterback, Mr. Sutton was also named to the Tennessee Sports
Writers Association All-State and Tennessee Football Coaches Association All-State teams and
the All-Region 1-3A first team; and
WHEREAS, Tyson Sutton completed 193 passes for 2,783 yards and 27 touchdowns
during the 2025 season and also scored two rushing touchdowns; and
WHEREAS, Tyson Sutton epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as he
has achieved a high level of success in sports while evincing great character both on and off the
field; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Sutton's notable achievement is a source of great pride for his family,
his community, and his school, and it is appropriate that we recognize this accomplished
athlete; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
SJR0850
013250
- 1 -

REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Tyson Sutton of
Gatlinburg-Pittman High School on being named to the All-County football team, wishing him
much success and happiness in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
